A cubic measurement is the three-dimensional derivative of a linear measure, so a cubic foot is defined as the volume of a cube with sides 1 ft in length. In metric terms a cubic foot is a cube with sides 0.3048 metres in length. One cubic foot is the equivalent to approximately 0.02831685 cubic metres, or 28.3169 litres. Cubic Kilometer. The cubic kilometer is a metric unit of volume equal to 1,000,000,000 cubic meters. The symbol of the cubic kilometer is km³ . 1 km3 = 1,000,000,000 m3 = 109 m3. To convert cubic kilometers to hm³, dam³, m³, dm³, cm³ and mm³ , multiply by one followed by as many trios of zeros as there are places between the cubic kilometer and the other unit. 1 km 3 = 1,000 hm 3 = 10 3 hm 3. 1 km 3 = 1,000,000 dam 3 = 10 6 dam 3. 1 km 3 = 1,000,000,000 m 3 = 10 9 m 3
